The paper proposes a deep neural network architecture for changepoint detection in multivariate time series data. This falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also deals with signal processing techniques such as wavelets and pyramid analysis, which are commonly used in the subfield of statistical signal processing (cs.ST). The proposed method involves the use of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also involves the use of convolutional neural networks for feature extraction, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV).
